# Python Code Quality

All Python code must pass the project's quality tools:

## Required Tools

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `black` | Code formatting |
| `isort` | Import sorting |
| `flake8` | Style linting |
| `mypy` | Type checking |
| `ruff` | Fast linting |
| `bandit` | Security scanning |

## Before Committing

```bash
black .
isort .
ruff check --fix .
mypy src/
bandit -r src/
```

## Standards

- Type hints on all public functions
- Docstrings on all public modules, classes, functions
- No `# type: ignore` without justification
- No security warnings from bandit
